======================================================================
  PART 3: H ≡ 0 (mod 7) — THE 7-BARRIER
======================================================================

H = 1 + 2α₁ + 4α₂ + 8α₃ + ...
H mod 7:
  1 + 2α₁ + 4α₂ + 1α₃ + 2α₄ + 4α₅ + ... (mod 7)
  (powers of 2 mod 7: 1,2,4,1,2,4,... period 3)

H ≡ 0 mod 7 requires: 1 + 2α₁ + 4α₂ ≡ 0 (mod 7)
i.e., 2α₁ + 4α₂ ≡ 6 (mod 7)
i.e., α₁ + 2α₂ ≡ 3 (mod 7)

At n=5: α₂=0, need α₁ ≡ 3 (mod 7)
But α₁ ∈ {0,1,2,4,5,6,7}, so α₁=3 impossible → H ≢ 0 (mod 7)

At n=6: need α₁ + 2α₂ ≡ 3 (mod 7)
This is a more complex constraint...

Computing α₁, α₂ at n=6...
Done: 18.6s

